A '''flightknife''' was the [[Adumar/Legends|Adumari]] equivalent of a fighter [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]]. It was generally built upon the same principles as squadrons serving with the [[New Republic Defense Force/Legends|Combined Defense Forces of the New Republic]] and the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]], however the tactics of the flightknife varied greatly as the object, according to Adumari tradition, was to kill the most prestigious [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] of the enemy flightknife first. The Adumari of [[Cartann]] had a long tradition of aerial "duels" that involved challenges issued to other flightknives; who could challenge and who could accept challanges varied and was the subject of a complicated series of rules and protocols.<ref name="X-Wing: Starfighters of Adumar ">''[[X-Wing: Starfighters of Adumar]]''</ref>

Further, during peacetime a flightknife seldom operated at full capacity; units based in Cartann, for example, often quartered as half-flightknives of six pilots apiece.<ref name="X-Wing: Starfighters of Adumar " />

